plantuml.content:
# PlantUML Charts

PlantUML focuses on UML modeling, suitable for detailed modeling of various software structures and behavior diagrams.

## UML Class Diagram

```plantuml
@startuml
class Animal {
    -name: String
    -age: int
    +eat()
}

class Dog {
    +bark()
}

Animal <|-- Dog
@enduml
```

## Sequence Diagram

```plantuml
@startuml
Alice -> Bob: Request
Bob --> Alice: Response
@enduml
```

## Activity Diagram

```plantuml
@startuml
start
:Process data;
if (Data valid?) then (yes)
  :Save data;
else (no)
  :Show error;
endif
stop
@enduml
```

## Notes

- PlantUML uses Pascal-like syntax
- Does not support Chinese identifiers
- Pay attention to layout controls such as `skinparam`

echarts.content:
# ECharts Charts

ECharts is suitable for creating data-driven, highly interactive visualization charts.

## Line Chart

```echarts
{
  "title": {
    "text": "Line Chart Example"
  },
  "xAxis": {
    "type": "category",
    "data": ["Mon", "Tue", "Wed", "Thu", "Fri", "Sat", "Sun"]
  },
  "yAxis": {
    "type": "value"
  },
  "series": [{
    "data": [150, 230, 224, 218, 135, 147, 260],
    "type": "line"
  }]
}
```

## Bar Chart

```echarts
{
  "title": {
    "text": "Bar Chart Example"
  },
  "xAxis": {
    "type": "category",
    "data": ["Mon", "Tue", "Wed", "Thu", "Fri", "Sat", "Sun"]
  },
  "yAxis": {
    "type": "value"
  },
  "series": [{
    "data": [120, 200, 150, 80, 70, 110, 130],
    "type": "bar"
  }]
}
```

## Pie Chart

```echarts
{
  "title": {
    "text": "Pie Chart Example"
  },
  "series": [{
    "type": "pie",
    "data": [
      {"value": 1048, "name": "Search Engine"},
      {"value": 735, "name": "Direct Access"},
      {"value": 580, "name": "Email Marketing"}
    ]
  }]
}
```

## Notes

- Configuration items must follow ECharts JSON format
- Templates can be obtained from ECharts official Option Builder
- Write the code block language as `echarts`, not `javascript`
- Code block contains only JSON format configuration items, no other content
